## Source of Truth

Before ANY change, read:

1. `/docs/features/vpn-feature-flyouts.md`
2. `/docs/features/_overview.md`

Use `Logic.md` (right panel & flyout hover logic) and `Design.md` (VPN Feature Flyouts).

## Reusable Components

From `/docs/features/vpn-feature-flyouts.md` — Dependencies on Shared Code:

| Path | Description |
|------|-------------|
| `src/imports/RightVpnFeatures.tsx` | `VpnFeatureType` must stay aligned |
| `src/app/components/flyout-icons/*` | SVG assets for flyout content |

If a shared component covers 80%+ of the requirement, extend it via props/config. Do NOT fork it. Do NOT create a parallel version.

## Feature-Specific Constraints

- Positioning is tied to map layout; verify against `Design.md` when changing offsets.
- Feature list in `RightVpnFeatures.tsx` and flyout content must stay in sync.

## Patterns to Follow

- Default export consumed by `WorldMap.tsx`; coordinate prop API with parent.

## What NOT to Do

- Do NOT duplicate icon assets from `flyout-icons/` or feature definitions from `RightVpnFeatures.tsx`.
- Do NOT change `VpnFeatureType` union without updating `RightVpnFeatures.tsx` and `/docs/features/vpn-feature-flyouts.md`.
- Do NOT add routes.
- Do NOT modify `WorldMap.tsx` integration without updating both feature docs when behavior changes.
